---
# Invoice & Payment Service — Cursor Rules

## Language & framework
- Go 1.22, chi router, GORM ORM, PostgreSQL
- No Rust, no TypeScript, no other languages

## Money — HARD RULE
- ALL money values are int64 representing cents (e.g. 1000 = $10.00)
- NEVER use float32, float64, or decimal for any money field
- Column names must end in _cents (e.g. total_cents, unit_amount_cents)
- Violating this rule is a critical bug

## Database
- Use GORM AutoMigrate only — never write raw SQL migration files
- Always call CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS pgcrypto before AutoMigrate
- Primary keys: uuid.UUID with gorm:"type:uuid;primaryKey;default:gen_random_uuid()"
- Money columns: gorm:"type:bigint;not null"

## Payment handler rules (payments.go) — follow EXACTLY
1. Check idempotency key FIRST before any DB transaction
2. Use SELECT FOR UPDATE inside a transaction to lock the invoice row
3. Insert payment_attempt with status="pending" BEFORE calling PSP
4. Commit the transaction BEFORE calling PSP
5. Set context.WithTimeout of 10 seconds on ALL PSP calls
6. After PSP response: update attempt + invoice in separate DB calls (no transaction needed)
7. NEVER call PSP inside a transaction

## Concurrency
- Row-level lock via raw SQL inside GORM transaction:
  tx.Raw("SELECT * FROM invoices WHERE id = ? FOR UPDATE", id).Scan(&invoice)
- Never use optimistic locking or advisory locks

## Webhooks
- ALWAYS dispatch webhooks in a goroutine: go webhook.Dispatch(...)
- NEVER block the API response waiting for webhook delivery
- Sign with HMAC-SHA256: X-Webhook-Signature: sha256=
- Include X-Webhook-Timestamp header

## Error responses
- ALL errors use this exact shape:
  {"error": {"code": "snake_case", "message": "Human readable"}}
- Use respondError(w, status, code, message) helper from handlers/helpers.go
- Never return plain text errors

## State machine — enforce these and only these transitions
  draft  → open          (POST /invoices/{id}/finalize)
  draft  → void          (POST /invoices/{id}/void)
  open   → paid          (POST /invoices/{id}/pay — PSP success)
  open   → void          (POST /invoices/{id}/void)
  open   → uncollectible (future: manual or dunning)
  paid, void, uncollectible → NOTHING (terminal, reject all with 409)

## Response format
- All responses: Content-Type: application/json
- Success: respond with the resource or { "data": [...], "count": N }
- Use respondJSON(w, status, data) helper from handlers/helpers.go

## Auth
- All routes except GET /health require Authorization: Bearer 
- Business ID from context: middleware.GetBusinessID(ctx)

## No floats — reminder
- Search for float before committing. If found anywhere in money path: fix it.
